cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.SI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a tool for automating a task that is typically done manually by app developers. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper involves designing a deep link model and analyzing the navigation graph of Android apps. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the limitations of current app interoperability and proposes a solution for enabling linked data between apps. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the user experience of accessing specific pages within an app and how deep links can improve this experience. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the potential value-added linked data between apps.
